<div class="comments-body">
<p>With your dual monitor, were you still able to get the tv tuner on your AIW to work? I have a similar setup with a 8500DV AIW and a PCI Xpert 128, but won't play TV when dual monitor is enabled.</p>
<span class="comments-post">Posted by <a href="mailto&#58;ctripled&#64;hotmail&#46;com">chuck</a> at March  8, 2003 11:21 PM</span>
</div>
<div class="comments-body">
<p>Chuck,</p>

<p>The issue you are facing is due likely to the fact that your AIW is not your primary graphics adapter. When using two GA's, the TV turner software looks to the primary adapter for the tuner function. If you have your AIW set as the secondary adapter or are booting with the secondary as the primary before windows loads, then this will happen. If you AIW is AGP, then you need to boot with the AGP as the primary. </p>

<p>Many people boot the PCI as primary in order to force windows to recognize and assign an IRQ to their PCI card...if you are having to do this, than you may need get another PCI card that is compatible with your other hardware...that or get a PCI AIW.</p>

<p>Hope this helps,<br />
cantedview</p>
<span class="comments-post">Posted by <a target="_blank" href="http://www.cantedview.com">cantedview</a> at March 15, 2004 06:02 AM</span>
</div>
